// TestCategoryC_TimingCorruptionVsCommit verifies correct handling of corruption
// that occurs in a race between scrub and commit operations.
//
// VERIFICATION GOALS:
// - Scrub and commit don't corrupt each other's invariants
// - Commit while scrub in-flight maintains data integrity
// - Scrub result accurate even if commit racing
// - No torn state transitions
//
// FAILURE SCENARIOS:
// - File 1 written, scrub started
// - File 2 commit racing with File 1 scrub
// - Corrupt File 1 between scrub detection and repair start
//
// EXPECTED OUTCOMES:
// - One operation (scrub or commit) takes precedence
// - Losing operation detects race and retries safely
// - No data corruption or invariant violation
func TestCategoryC_TimingCorruptionVsCommit(t *testing.T) {
	t.Skip("Category C not yet implemented: requires synchronization point simulation and timing injection")

	// PSEUDOCODE:
	// 1. Write file1, inject timing hook in scrub path
